"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses library scikit-learn. The issue lies in the way the ColumnTransformer is used with the Pipeline. The ColumnTransformer is correctly defined, but the GaussianNB algorithm in the Pipeline does not support the output of the ColumnTransformer which is a numpy array with more than 2 features for the OneHotEncoder part. GaussianNB expects non-negative feature values but OneHotEncoder outputs 0s and 1s which can be considered as indicators of categories. However, the MinMaxScaler outputs float values which can be negative and can be considered as non-indicator features.\",\n  \"patch\": \"26c26\\n< ('algo', GaussianNB())\\n---\\n> ('algo', GaussianNB(var_smoothing=1e-9))\\nHowever, this may still not work because GaussianNB is not suitable for categorical data. Consider using a different algorithm like LogisticRegression or DecisionTreeClassifier.\\nAlternatively, 26c26\\n< ('algo', GaussianNB())\\n---\\n> ('algo', LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000))\\n\"\n}"